quran[9]{c,v,t}:
  40,8,"Our Lord, show them into the Gardens of Eden (gardens of eternity) which You have promised them, and whoever among their forefathers, spouses and off-spring have acted honorably. You are the Powerful, the Wise!"
  40,9,"Shield them from evil deeds. You will show mercy on that day to anyone You shield from evil deeds. That will be the supreme Achievement!""
  40,10,"The ones who disbelieve will be addressed [as follows]: "Allah (God)'s disgust [during your life] will be even greater than your own disgust is towards yourselves [during your torment] when you are called upon to believe and [still] disbelieve.""
  40,11,"They will say: "Our Lord, You have let us die twice and have revived us twice, and so we [now] acknowledge our sins. Is there no way to escape from here?""
  40,12,"This has happened because you disbelieved when Allah (God) was invoked in His Oneness, while if others were associated with him, you would believe. Discretion belongs to Allah (God), the Sublime, the Great."
  40,13,"He is the One Who shows you His signs and sends you down sustenance from the sky. Yet only someone who repents will bear this in mind."
  40,14,"So, appeal to Allah (God) sincerely; worship belongs to Him even though disbelievers may hate [to admit] it."
  40,15,"Lofty in rank, Possessor of the Throne, He drops the Spirit of His bidding on any of Hi servants He may wish, so he may warn about the day of the Meeting,"
  40,16,"the day when they will [all] emerge. Nothing concerning them is hidden from Allah (God). Who holds control today? Allah (God) Alone, the Irresistible hold it!"